snippet: Disappointed liberals are complaining that President Obama caved in on taxes and sent a signal that he would ultimately surrender on other priorities.
abstract: White House Memo; fiscal cliff deal marks end of four years of debate between Pres Obama and Republicans about raising taxes on wealthy, but also seems to reopen debate within Democratic Party about nature of his leadership and his skills as negotiator; disappointed liberals complain that Obama has caved on taxes and sent signal that he will ultimately surrender on other priorities.
lead_paragraph: Disappointed liberals are complaining that President Obama caved in on taxes and sent a signal that he would ultimately surrender on other priorities.

headline.main: On the Left, Seeing Obama Giving Away Too Much, Again
headline.print_headline: On the Left, Seeing Obama Giving Away Too Much, Again
